(c) use the R function ARMAtoMA() to determine the first 20 𝜓-weights in the causal representation 𝑋𝑡=∑∞𝑗=0𝜓𝑗𝑊𝑡−𝑗. Use those 𝜓 weights to approximate the corresponding ACF values 𝜌(ℎ) , ℎ=0,1,2,3

psi_coefs <- c(1, ARMAtoMA(ar=c(1.6,-0.64), lag.max=20))

gamma_0 = sum(psi_coefs^2)

gamma_1 = 0
for (j in 1:20) {
  i = j+1
  num = psi_coefs[j] * psi_coefs[i]
  gamma_1 = gamma_1 + num
}

gamma_2 = 0
for (j in 1:19) {
  i = j+2
  num = psi_coefs[j] * psi_coefs[i]
  gamma_2 = gamma_2 + num
}

gamma_3 = 0
for (j in 1:18) {
  i = j+2
  num = psi_coefs[j] * psi_coefs[i]
  gamma_3 = gamma_3 + num
}

rhos = c(1, gamma_1 / gamma_0, gamma_2 / gamma_0, gamma_3 / gamma_0)


acf(psi_coefs, lag.max = 20, demean = F )

Question 6

File HW4_Q6_data.csv (available in the folder “Datasets”) contains a time series observations for time t = 1,2,…,900

(a) plot the time series. Is there an apparent departure from stationarity?

library('astsa')
data = read.csv('HW4_Q6_data.csv')
data = ts(data)
tsplot(data, col = 4)

There is not an apparent departure from stationarity.

(b) Determine an appropriate ARMA model for the data. Explain how you determined the order of the model.

acf(data)

acf(data, type = 'partial')

The appropiate model for this process is an AR(2) and we obtained this by observing the ACF and PACF plots. The ACF tails off while the PACF cuts off at p = 2.

(c) Based on your answer in part (b), estimate the parameters of the ARMA model and construct a 95% confidence interval for the estimated coefficients.

acf_data = acf(data)

rho_1 = acf_data[[1]][2]
rho_2 = acf_data[[1]][3]
gamma_0 = sum((data - mean(data))^2) / 900
R = matrix(c(1, rho_1, rho_1, 1), nrow = 2)
phi_data = solve(R)%*%c(rho_1, rho_2)
sigma_squared = gamma_0 * (1 - t(c(rho_1, rho_2))%*%phi_data)

n = length(data)
s = as.vector(sigma_squared / (n * gamma_0)) * solve(R)
est1_ci = c(phi_data[1] - 1.96 * s[1,1], phi_data[1] + 1.96 * s[1,1])
           
est2_ci = c(phi_data[2] - 1.96 * s[2,2], phi_data[2] + 1.96 * s[2,2])

The estimated parameters are as follows:
